@multiarg strategy/globe6-devmap
@title Strategy Development Map — `🌐6` Recursive Substrate Closure
@audience futon-devs, war-machine-operators, future-you
@tone formal-analytic
@style roadmap
@factor Equanimity / Closure (upekkhā)
@IFR: `🌐6` turns the stack's self-model from asserted architecture into a
running, evidence-producing recursive substrate whose recommendations bind to
real work and feed counter-deltas back into the next pass.
@state (2026-04-25) `🌐6` is disambiguated from Argument `💼6`, and the closure
rubric is now explicit. The live gap remains: Portfolio Inference self-step
count is still zero, downstream binding targets are not yet projected into
operator handles, and Hypergraph Operator remains spec-only.
@next Step Portfolio Inference once against `THE-STACK`; emit durable evidence
for the run; bind the resulting recommendation to finite operational handles;
show at least one downstream counter delta reflected in the next recommendation
surface.

## The Argument

`🌐6` is the stack-level recursive substrate:

- Mission Control observes
- Portfolio Inference chooses
- Hypergraph Operator generalises

At present, the War Machine can recommend "Close `🌐6`", but the recommendation
is only strategically legible. It is not yet operationally closed because the
recursive loop has not been stepped on itself, its outputs are not yet bound to
finite operator handles, and there is no durable proof that downstream counter
changes revise the upstream model on the next pass.

This strategy devmap exists to make `🌐6` closure falsifiable.


! instantiated-by: Prototype 0 — First Self-Step Witness [🪜/证 🌐/始]
  :maturity :greenfield
  :owner :stack
  :actual-status :greenfield
  :depends-on [f3/P2 f3/P3 f3c/P0]
  :evidence-for-active [The closure rubric, stack AIF story, and recommendation-binding mission now agree that "Close 🌐6" requires a real self-step rather than prose]

  + context: The current open claim is that the recursive substrate exists architecturally, but no durable run shows Portfolio Inference consuming the stack's own self-description as input.
  + IF: You want `🌐6` to mean more than "a recommendation exists"
  + HOWEVER: A recommendation with `pi_self_step_count = 0` is still upstream-only theatre
  + THEN: Run Portfolio Inference once against `THE-STACK` / leaf-registry state and persist the resulting self-step as durable evidence
  + BECAUSE: A first self-step is the minimum event that falsifies the claim that the recursive substrate is still wholly uninhabited

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[futon5a/holes/excursions/E-globe-6-closure-rubric.md defines Open vs Stepped and the first three machine predicates]
    evidence[futon5a/holes/stories/THE-STACK.aif.edn states the open gap: PI loop step-count = 0; HGO spec-only]
    evidence[futon5a/holes/missions/M-recommendation-bindings.md identifies the current recommendation surface as asserted rather than operationally bound]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Define the durable evidence shape for a `🌐6` self-step: input snapshot ref, ranked actions, selected action, confidence, timestamp]
    next[Run PI once with `THE-STACK` as the observed substrate and persist the result]
    next[Expose that evidence ref from the War Machine recommendation surface]

  :success-criteria
    pass[`pi_self_step_count > 0`]
    pass[`pi_self_last_run_at != nil`]
    pass[`pi_self_evidence_ref != nil`]
    fail[`🌐6` can still be recommended without any durable self-step evidence]

  :psr-example "Selected first self-step witness because the recursive substrate must leave a durable trace before any stronger closure claim is honest"
  :pur-template "`🌐6` self-step {{run-id}} persisted with input {{snapshot-ref}} and selected action {{action-id}}"


! instantiated-by: Prototype 1 — Repeatable Heartbeat [💓/循 🌐/住]
  :maturity :greenfield
  :owner :stack
  :actual-status :greenfield
  :depends-on [f3/P3 f3c/P0]
  :evidence-for-active [The rubric distinguishes one-off stepping from an inhabited loop with repeated cycles and live readout]

  + context: One self-step proves executability, but not inhabitation.
  + IF: You want `🌐6` to be a running substrate rather than a one-off demonstration
  + HOWEVER: A single step with no second cycle and no prediction-error readout is still demo-ware
  + THEN: Repeat the self-step across more than one cycle and emit heartbeat / prediction-error evidence visible to operators or agents
  + BECAUSE: Inhabitation begins when the loop can run again and its state transitions remain visible over time

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[futon5a/holes/excursions/E-globe-6-closure-rubric.md defines Inhabited as repeated cycles plus a live recommendation readout]
    evidence[futon3/library/realtime/liveness-heartbeats.flexiarg argues that durable loop signals need explicit heartbeat semantics]
    evidence[futon3/library/futon-theory/progress-signal.flexiarg constrains progress claims to observable signals rather than narration]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Define the `🌐6` heartbeat event shape and prediction-error counters]
    next[Run more than one self-step cycle and append the sequence durably]
    next[Show the latest `🌐6` cycle status from an operator-facing surface]

  :success-criteria
    pass[`pi_self_heartbeat_cycles >= 1`]
    pass[At least two durable `🌐6` self-step records exist]
    pass[A live operator surface can point at the most recent `🌐6` cycle]
    fail[`🌐6` still depends on one-off manual narration to claim inhabitation]

  :psr-example "Selected repeatable heartbeat because closure claims require a running loop, not a screenshot of one run"
  :pur-template "`🌐6` cycle {{run-id}} advanced heartbeat count to {{count}} with prediction error {{delta}}"


! instantiated-by: Prototype 2 — Binding Surface [🪢/定 🌐/指]
  :maturity :greenfield
  :owner :stack
  :actual-status :greenfield
  :depends-on [f3/P2 f3c/P0]
  :evidence-for-active [The recommendation-bindings mission already names candidate binding targets but they are not yet wired]

  + context: A recommendation becomes actionable only when it projects into a finite list of handles the operator can actually move.
  + IF: You want "Close `🌐6`" to answer "what do I do next?"
  + HOWEVER: A recommendation with no downstream handles remains strategically legible but operationally theatrical
  + THEN: Bind `🌐6` recommendations to concrete targets: candidate invariant families, live violations, `boundary.edn` entries, and mission / prototype handles
  + BECAUSE: A finite binding surface is what turns a strategy handle into executable work

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[futon5a/holes/missions/M-recommendation-bindings.md identifies boundary tuples, invariant queues, and live violations as the missing downstream handles]
    evidence[futon5a/holes/excursions/E-globe-6-closure-rubric.md defines Bound in terms of finite operational handles and visible downstream counters]
    evidence[futon3/scripts/devmap_readiness.py already emits boundary tuples that can anchor strategy bindings]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Choose the first bound target family for `🌐6` (boundary tuple, invariant queue, or live violation list)]
    next[Emit `wm_binding_target_count(🌐6)` from the recommendation surface]
    next[Let operators click through from `🌐6` to the bound target list]

  :success-criteria
    pass[`wm_binding_target_count(🌐6) > 0`]
    pass[The operator can enumerate a finite list of items to advance `🌐6`]
    pass[At least one visible downstream counter is attached to the recommendation]
    fail[`🌐6` remains a slogan with no bound operational handles]

  :psr-example "Selected binding surface because a strategy handle without concrete targets cannot participate in the stack's proof path"
  :pur-template "`🌐6` now binds to {{count}} targets across {{surface}} with visible counter {{counter-id}}"


! instantiated-by: Prototype 3 — Counter-Linked Closure [🔁/验 🌐/合]
  :maturity :greenfield
  :owner :stack
  :actual-status :greenfield
  :depends-on [f3/P3 f3c/P0]
  :evidence-for-active [The rubric defines Closed-for-now as downstream action producing a counter delta that revises the upstream model]

  + context: Bound recommendations still do not close `🌐6` unless downstream work changes what the upstream model believes on the next pass.
  + IF: You want the War Machine to learn from whether a `🌐6` recommendation actually moved the stack
  + HOWEVER: Without counter-linked revision, the loop only points downstream and never closes back upstream
  + THEN: Take at least one `🌐6`-bound action, observe a real counter delta, and update the upstream recommendation state from that result
  + BECAUSE: The first honest closure event is recommendation -> action -> counter change -> model revision

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[futon5a/holes/excursions/E-globe-6-closure-rubric.md defines Closed-for-now as all seven predicates becoming true]
    evidence[futon3/library/futon-theory/counter-ratchet.flexiarg requires closure claims to attach to counter movement rather than narration]
    evidence[futon3/library/aif/policy-precision-commitment-temperature.flexiarg constrains policy revision to explicit evidence about changed conditions]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Select one `🌐6`-bound action and record its before/after counter state]
    next[Emit `wm_binding_counter_delta_count(🌐6)` and `wm_upstream_update_observed?(🌐6)`]
    next[Change the next recommendation surface as a function of the observed result]

  :success-criteria
    pass[`wm_binding_counter_delta_count(🌐6) > 0`]
    pass[`wm_upstream_update_observed?(🌐6) = true`]
    pass[The next `🌐6` recommendation changes because of observed downstream results]
    fail[Operators still have to narrate closure manually]

  :psr-example "Selected counter-linked closure because only an upstream revision proves the substrate is learning from its own recommendations"
  :pur-template "`🌐6` action {{action-id}} changed counter {{counter-id}} by {{delta}} and revised next recommendation to {{next-id}}"


! instantiated-by: Prototype 4 — Hypergraph Generalisation Handoff [🕸️/升 🌐/广]
  :maturity :greenfield
  :owner :stack
  :actual-status :greenfield
  :depends-on [f3/P1 f3/P2 f3/P3]
  :evidence-for-active [The THE-STACK gap explicitly says HGO is still spec-only, so the substrate is not fully recursive until generalisation leaves the spec layer]

  + context: `🌐6` names a triad, not just Mission Control plus Portfolio Inference.
  + IF: You want the full recursive substrate rather than a two-stage observation/selection loop
  + HOWEVER: As long as Hypergraph Operator remains spec-only, the stack still cannot generalise new strategic structure from its own observed tensions
  + THEN: Hand durable `🌐6` evidence into a concrete HGO generalisation pass that emits a new candidate pattern, edge, or binding rule
  + BECAUSE: The recursive substrate is only complete when observed tensions can be generalised back into stack structure

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[futon5a/holes/stories/THE-STACK.aif.edn names HGO spec-only as part of the open `🌐6` gap]
    evidence[futon3/library/futon-theory/baldwin-cycle.flexiarg describes the stack's generalisation ratchet from evidence back into canon]
    evidence[futon3/library/sidecar/explicit-promotion-to-facts.flexiarg constrains how fuzzy observations become durable structural updates]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Choose the first HGO output shape for `🌐6`: candidate pattern, candidate edge, or candidate binding rule]
    next[Attach one HGO output to a prior `🌐6` counter-linked closure event]
    next[Show that the generalised output re-enters the next recommendation cycle]

  :success-criteria
    pass[At least one HGO artefact is emitted from durable `🌐6` evidence]
    pass[The HGO artefact is inspectable and linked back to its source run]
    pass[The generated artefact re-enters the next strategy pass as input]
    fail[HGO remains prose-only while `🌐6` claims full recursive closure]

  :psr-example "Selected HGO handoff because the recursive substrate is incomplete if it can observe and choose but never generalise"
  :pur-template "`🌐6` generalised {{artefact-id}} from run {{run-id}} and fed it into the next substrate pass"
